WEBVTT

00:06.083 --> 00:08.958
[Galadriel]  My brother gave his life
hunting Sauron.

00:09.083 --> 00:10.833
His task is now mine.

00:12.250 --> 00:13.791
[Thondir]  Commander Galadriel.

00:13.916 --> 00:17.375
This company has followed you
to the very edge of the world.

00:17.500 --> 00:20.000
It's been years
since the last Orc was sighted.

00:21.125 --> 00:24.458
[Galadriel]  This mark's very existence
proves Sauron escaped.

00:24.833 --> 00:26.208
The question now is, where?

00:26.291 --> 00:27.166
The evil is gone.

00:27.250 --> 00:29.708
Then why is it not gone from in here?

00:29.791 --> 00:33.375
[Gil-galad]  These heroes shall be granted
a passage across the sea

00:33.416 --> 00:35.166
to dwell for all eternity.

00:35.291 --> 00:37.416
[Elrond]  You have fought
long enough, Galadriel.

00:37.500 --> 00:38.541
[whooshing]

00:38.625 --> 00:39.625
Put up your sword.

00:39.916 --> 00:41.416
[Galadriel]  Without it, what am I to be?

00:43.791 --> 00:44.666
[whooshing]

00:45.125 --> 00:48.833
Are you acquainted
with the work of Lord Celebrimbor?

00:48.916 --> 00:51.250
[Elrond]  The greatest
of Elven-smiths, of course.

00:52.791 --> 00:54.291
What's one of them doing here?

00:56.041 --> 00:58.041
She's got some sort of a sickness.

00:58.166 --> 01:01.458
-Where has she been grazing?
-She wandered east a few days ago.

01:01.541 --> 01:02.375
How far east?

01:02.666 --> 01:03.500
[Bronwyn] Hordern.

01:05.625 --> 01:07.583
[voices whispering in Black Speech]

01:08.000 --> 01:10.791
[Nori]  Haven't you ever wondered
what else is out there?

01:10.916 --> 01:12.166
Beyond our wanderin'.

01:12.250 --> 01:14.833
Nobody goes off trail
and nobody walks alone.

01:15.791 --> 01:18.458
-[Sadoc]  The skies are strange.
-[whooshing]

01:18.625 --> 01:20.000
[explosion]

01:26.625 --> 01:28.625
[theme music playing]

02:59.416 --> 03:01.666
[breathing echoing]

03:23.541 --> 03:25.250
[panting]

03:36.666 --> 03:39.666
[crackling]

03:56.208 --> 03:58.458
-Nori!
-[gasps] Poppy!

03:58.541 --> 04:01.166
Have the wheels come off your cart?
Get away from there!

04:01.250 --> 04:02.291
Shh!

04:02.541 --> 04:04.666
You shouldn't sneak up on folk like that.

04:04.750 --> 04:06.000
-Well, you shouldn't be here.
-Shh!

04:06.083 --> 04:07.541
[both gasping, exclaiming]

04:11.958 --> 04:13.125
[whispering] It's not hot.

04:13.208 --> 04:14.583
[Poppy whispering] Fine. It's not hot.

04:14.666 --> 04:17.875
Doesn't change the fact
that there's a giant in there.

04:18.250 --> 04:21.708
She's making that face.
Not that face, Nori...

04:23.625 --> 04:24.458
Nori!

04:25.958 --> 04:26.791
Nori, don't!

04:31.000 --> 04:33.708
[Nori gasping]

04:37.250 --> 04:39.333
[panting]

04:43.458 --> 04:46.458
Nori, don't! He's dead! Come on!

04:48.541 --> 04:49.500
[screaming]

04:49.583 --> 04:53.583
-No! Don't! Don't! Please!
-[indistinct shouting echoing]

05:00.833 --> 05:01.666
[gasps]

05:01.750 --> 05:05.250
[whooshing]

05:06.583 --> 05:07.708
No!

05:15.458 --> 05:19.458
[wind whistling]

05:21.500 --> 05:25.333
[whooshing]

05:26.083 --> 05:27.083
What...

05:28.583 --> 05:30.666
[gasping]

05:36.083 --> 05:37.041
[gasps]

05:37.125 --> 05:38.458
Your mam's gonna kill ya.

05:40.375 --> 05:44.541
You're not telling her.
Neither am I. Quick sticks.

05:44.625 --> 05:47.041
We can't leave him like this
or the wolves will get him.

05:47.125 --> 05:48.916
-So?
-So, that's not who we are.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.291
That's not who you are.

05:50.375 --> 05:53.625
I can't carry him alone.
Are you gonna help me or not?

05:53.708 --> 05:54.958
-Not.
-Poppy!

05:55.708 --> 05:58.333
How exactly are we supposed
to carry a giant?

05:59.916 --> 06:01.666
[whispering] Must've been a star fall.

06:03.958 --> 06:05.666
A big one.

06:05.750 --> 06:08.166
How many signs do you need?

06:09.083 --> 06:11.958
Ask me, we ought to break camp
this moment.

06:12.041 --> 06:13.541
-[sighs]
-What about the festival?

06:13.625 --> 06:15.833
Let's not do anything rash just yet.

06:15.916 --> 06:18.916
More'n likely we're safer in camp
than we are out.

06:19.541 --> 06:21.541
But keep an eye out, the both of you.

06:21.625 --> 06:23.333
-Malva's right.
-Yes.

06:23.416 --> 06:26.125
This does not bode well.

06:26.208 --> 06:28.041
Now, away with you. Go on.

06:28.125 --> 06:29.333
[snaps fingers] Pssk!

06:29.416 --> 06:32.333
-All right, all right, all right.
-Go on. Hurry up.

06:33.083 --> 06:34.791
[rustling]

06:42.583 --> 06:44.458
-[rustling]
-[gasping]

06:47.291 --> 06:49.000
-[rustling]
-[gasps]

06:52.458 --> 06:54.458
Look at him. He's bleeding massive.

06:54.541 --> 06:56.833
-He's got to be...
-He's not a troll!

06:56.916 --> 06:59.250
All right, smart-foot. Then what is he?

06:59.333 --> 07:02.166
Uh, maybe he's big folk.

07:02.250 --> 07:03.666
Human?

07:03.750 --> 07:05.666
[scoffs] No way. He'd be squished.

07:05.750 --> 07:07.000
Elf, maybe?

07:07.500 --> 07:10.208
-Wrong ears. And he's not handsome.
-[laughs]

07:10.291 --> 07:12.916
Not to mention,
Elves don't fall from the sky.

07:13.000 --> 07:14.791
Nobody does. As far as I know.

07:14.875 --> 07:15.875
He did.

07:15.958 --> 07:18.708
-Are you even pullin'?
-Yeah, of course I'm pullin'!

07:18.791 --> 07:20.708
-Well, pull harder!
-Shh!

07:21.916 --> 07:24.458
This is ludicrous.
He's never gonna fit in that old cart.

07:24.541 --> 07:25.958
It's just for one night.

07:26.041 --> 07:29.916
In the mornin', we'll pack him up
some food and send him on his way.

07:30.000 --> 07:32.375
-What way?
-That's a tomorrow problem.

07:32.458 --> 07:35.166
-This isn't an adventure.
-What's that supposed to mean?

07:35.250 --> 07:37.958
-I didn't go looking for this.
-But you're not turning away.

07:38.041 --> 07:40.541
-Because I can't.
-Because you won't.

07:40.625 --> 07:43.458
This stranger isn't a Man, or an Elf,

07:43.541 --> 07:45.500
or some baby eagle with a broken wing.

07:45.583 --> 07:47.500
-That was one time.
-He's something else.

07:47.583 --> 07:48.500
[thuds]

07:48.583 --> 07:50.250
[both panting]

07:51.125 --> 07:52.791
[sighs] Maybe he's something dangerous.

07:52.875 --> 07:55.083
Now you sound
just like Malva and the sisters.

07:55.166 --> 07:56.291
Oh, it's not just them.

07:56.375 --> 07:58.833
Anybody finds out
that we helped a stranger,

07:58.916 --> 08:01.708
and anything bad that happens
the next three seasons

08:01.791 --> 08:03.083
will be our fault.

08:03.166 --> 08:06.458
If a fog lasts a little too long,
a wheel gets stuck in a rut...

08:06.875 --> 08:08.416
Oh, great goats!

08:08.500 --> 08:09.750
[Poppy] Faster, before it crashes!

08:09.833 --> 08:11.375
[Nori] Oh, so now you care about him.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.958
[Poppy] No, no!
The wheelbarrow, it's not mine!

08:14.041 --> 08:16.541
[crickets chirping]

08:25.916 --> 08:28.083
-[laughs]
-[The Stranger mumbles]

08:42.833 --> 08:44.666
[snoring]

09:01.208 --> 09:02.708
Why you doing this, Nori?

09:03.958 --> 09:06.375
-I feel like he's my responsibility.
-You feel like everyone

09:06.458 --> 09:08.291
-is your responsibility.
-No.

09:09.125 --> 09:10.625
This is different.

09:15.916 --> 09:18.750
He could've landed anywhere,
and he landed here.

09:21.041 --> 09:25.875
I know it sounds strange,
but somehow I just know he's important.

09:27.333 --> 09:29.833
It's like there's a reason this happened.

09:29.916 --> 09:32.625
Like I was supposed to find him. Me.

09:34.125 --> 09:37.625
I can't walk away from that.
Not till I know he's safe.

09:40.541 --> 09:41.583
Can you?

09:44.666 --> 09:46.250
Fine. I won't tell anyone.

09:48.625 --> 09:49.875
Thank you.

09:53.333 --> 09:55.750
[Poppy] What does a giant eat, anyway?

09:55.833 --> 09:57.791
Hope it's not Harfoots.

09:57.875 --> 10:00.375
[Nori] Just the ones
that can't keep a secret.

10:00.750 --> 10:03.541
[crickets chirping]

10:03.666 --> 10:06.083
[fire crackling]

10:08.750 --> 10:11.708
[creaking]

10:29.000 --> 10:31.416
[Bronwyn]
The earth is riven with fissures.

10:31.500 --> 10:33.166
Like in a ground-shake.

10:35.416 --> 10:36.500
[Arondir] No bodies.

10:39.208 --> 10:40.583
No wounded.

10:40.666 --> 10:42.083
Perhaps they all fled.

10:42.166 --> 10:43.000
[flies buzzing]

10:43.083 --> 10:44.250
[Arondir] Perhaps.

10:45.291 --> 10:46.500
[latch opening]

10:59.375 --> 11:00.791
This was Ciaran's home.

11:01.458 --> 11:05.500
And... Hana. His wife was Hana.

11:08.958 --> 11:12.291
This was no ground-shake.
Someone dug this passage.

11:12.375 --> 11:13.541
Something.

11:14.333 --> 11:15.750
Men did not do this.

11:15.833 --> 11:18.208
Go. Warn your people.

11:18.625 --> 11:20.166
You're not coming with me?

11:20.250 --> 11:21.916
I must follow the passage.
The other direction.

11:22.000 --> 11:25.833
-You don't know what's down there.
-That is the reason I must go.

11:33.333 --> 11:35.000
[sighs]

11:41.833 --> 11:43.333
[wind whistling]

12:03.208 --> 12:05.541
[birds chirping]

12:05.625 --> 12:06.958
[Elrond] FÃ«anor's hammer.

12:08.833 --> 12:11.666
The tool that wrought the Silmarils.

12:13.583 --> 12:16.500
The jewels that contain
the very light of Valinor.

12:17.333 --> 12:18.666
Strange, isn't it?

12:19.500 --> 12:23.333
How one object could be responsible
for creating so much beauty...

12:24.416 --> 12:25.666
And so much pain.

12:26.250 --> 12:29.375
True creation requires sacrifice.

12:31.333 --> 12:35.750
They say that Morgoth
found the Silmarils so beautiful

12:37.083 --> 12:39.083
that after he'd stolen them, for weeks,

12:39.166 --> 12:41.875
he could do nothing
but stare into their depths.

12:41.958 --> 12:43.041
Hmm.

12:43.125 --> 12:46.333
It was only after one of his tears
fell upon the jewels

12:46.416 --> 12:49.291
and he was faced with the evil
of his own reflection,

12:49.375 --> 12:51.541
that the reverie was finally broken.

12:53.000 --> 12:55.166
From that moment, he...

12:55.250 --> 12:57.416
He looked upon their light no more.

12:58.416 --> 12:59.416
[sighs]

13:00.500 --> 13:04.666
FÃ«anor's work nearly turned the heart
of the Great Foe himself. [laughs]

13:06.791 --> 13:08.708
What has mine ever accomplished?

13:09.625 --> 13:12.125
I... It has turned my heart, my lord.

13:12.208 --> 13:13.791
The heart of many an Elf.

13:15.000 --> 13:17.791
But I aspire to do far more than that.

13:18.666 --> 13:21.250
An Age ago, our kind brought war
to these shores.

13:21.333 --> 13:22.958
I want to fill them with beauty.

13:23.041 --> 13:27.708
To grow beyond petty works of jewel-craft,
and devise something of real power.

13:28.333 --> 13:30.250
What is it you hope to craft?

13:30.333 --> 13:33.750
"What" is but a glint on the far horizon.

13:33.833 --> 13:39.250
You have come to Eregion
to help me achieve the "how."

13:40.333 --> 13:41.500
A tower?

13:42.250 --> 13:47.416
[Celebrimbor] One that can host a forge
more powerful than any ever built.

13:47.500 --> 13:50.583
Able to birth a flame as hot
as a dragon's tongue,

13:50.666 --> 13:52.166
and as pure as starlight.

13:52.250 --> 13:56.083
The things we could use it to create
could transform Middle-earth.

13:56.166 --> 13:57.958
What seems to be the difficulty?

13:58.916 --> 14:00.916
I need it completed by spring.

14:02.250 --> 14:04.250
My lord, that would require a...

14:04.333 --> 14:06.625
A workforce greater
than any ever assembled.

14:06.708 --> 14:09.500
Yes. The High King cannot provide one.

14:09.583 --> 14:12.000
So he has sent me you instead.

14:15.625 --> 14:19.958
Have you considered seeking partners
outside the confines of our own race?

14:20.666 --> 14:22.166
How far outside?

14:34.000 --> 14:37.000
[wind whooshing]

14:44.250 --> 14:46.458
[Celebrimbor]
An alliance with the Dwarves would be

14:46.541 --> 14:48.500
the diplomatic achievement of the age.

14:48.583 --> 14:51.583
[Elrond] Their prince, Durin,
is an old and dear friend.

14:51.666 --> 14:53.166
Almost like a brother to me.

14:53.250 --> 14:57.333
[Celebrimbor] I've heard the Dwarves
have greatly expanded their halls of late.

14:57.666 --> 15:00.250
They... They sculpt the rock

15:01.291 --> 15:05.333
with the respect of one
who cares for an aged parent.

15:05.416 --> 15:08.083
I've long wanted to see them work.

15:08.166 --> 15:10.083
I had no idea you admired them so.

15:10.166 --> 15:12.791
I admire all who can see
into the mystery of things,

15:12.875 --> 15:15.541
who can divine
from the plainness of what is,

15:15.625 --> 15:17.416
the beauty of what could be...

15:18.583 --> 15:21.666
Might your friend be able to grant me
access to their workshops?

15:21.750 --> 15:24.625
[Elrond] Oh, if I know Durin,
he'll do far more than that.

15:25.375 --> 15:27.375
He'll welcome us with open arms,

15:27.458 --> 15:29.291
rams' horns blaring,

15:29.416 --> 15:31.250
tables filled with salted pork,

15:31.333 --> 15:34.000
-and enough malt beer to fill the Anduin.
-[scraping]

15:34.083 --> 15:35.625
[Dwarf] What do you want?

15:36.500 --> 15:38.208
It is Elrond of Lindon,

15:38.291 --> 15:40.875
accompanied by Celebrimbor,
Lord of Eregion.

15:41.625 --> 15:43.583
We seek an audience with Prince Durin.

15:44.958 --> 15:46.625
-[Dwarf] No.
-[scraping]

15:51.791 --> 15:52.958
My apologies.

15:54.166 --> 15:57.041
Inform Lord Durin
that his friend, Elrond...

15:57.125 --> 15:59.708
[Dwarf] His judgment
has already been rendered, Elf.

16:03.500 --> 16:04.791
Rams' horns?

16:19.041 --> 16:20.500
All right, then, my friend.

16:27.583 --> 16:30.625
I invoke the Rite of  Sigin-tarÃ¢g.

16:30.708 --> 16:32.250
What is the Rite of...

16:32.333 --> 16:35.083
[loud creaking, rumbling]

16:37.125 --> 16:39.125
-[Dwarf commands in Khuzdul]
-[Dwarves grunt]

16:39.208 --> 16:40.583
[in English] I'll rejoin you in Eregion.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.250
Are you certain
you know what you're doing?

16:42.333 --> 16:44.458
Lord Celebrimbor, trust me.

16:44.541 --> 16:47.333
You are master of your craft, my friend.

16:47.416 --> 16:50.166
Allow me a few days to work mine.

16:52.000 --> 16:52.833
[Dwarf grunts]

16:55.500 --> 16:56.666
[Dwarf commands in Khuzdul]

17:03.750 --> 17:07.208
[creaking]

17:07.250 --> 17:08.250
[clanks]

17:15.208 --> 17:16.458
[axes clank]

17:19.750 --> 17:21.625
[exclaims in Quenya]  ElmendÃ©a...

17:27.833 --> 17:29.958
[Dwarf grunts]

17:44.416 --> 17:47.083
[Dwarves chattering in Khuzdul]

18:04.583 --> 18:09.541
[Dwarves chanting in unison]

18:18.041 --> 18:21.000
[horn blowing]

18:23.625 --> 18:27.166
[chanting intensifies]

18:29.625 --> 18:30.583
[chanting stops]

18:30.666 --> 18:34.458
-[shouts] Khazad!
-[Dwarves] DÃ»m!

18:34.541 --> 18:36.666
[Dwarves laughing]

18:37.833 --> 18:39.541
My heart sings to see you, old...

18:39.625 --> 18:44.833
The Elf Elrond has invoked
the Rite of  Sigin-tarÃ¢g.

18:44.916 --> 18:46.666
[Dwarves laughing]

18:46.791 --> 18:49.583
The Dwarven test of endurance,

18:49.666 --> 18:52.250
fashioned by AulÃ« himself.

18:52.333 --> 18:53.916
[Dwarves agreeing]

18:54.375 --> 18:57.125
Once we lift our hammers,

18:58.291 --> 19:02.333
we shall break the great stones
until one of us can break no more.

19:02.416 --> 19:04.208
[Dwarves cheering]

19:05.208 --> 19:07.291
Should the Elf forfeit,

19:08.041 --> 19:11.291
he will be banished
from all Dwarven lands.

19:11.375 --> 19:12.750
[Dwarves agreeing]

19:12.958 --> 19:14.125
Forever!

19:14.250 --> 19:18.416
[Dwarves laughing, cheering]

19:19.500 --> 19:21.916
Does the Elf understand?

19:24.166 --> 19:25.333
The Elf does.

19:26.291 --> 19:29.541
In the unlikely event
the Elf should win...

19:29.666 --> 19:32.541
-[laughs]
-[Dwarves laughing]

19:32.625 --> 19:36.208
We shall grant a single boon.
But should he lose...

19:36.291 --> 19:39.166
Banished. Yes. Understood.

19:39.250 --> 19:40.583
[mockingly] Mmm.

19:44.208 --> 19:45.458
Begin!

19:46.375 --> 19:48.166
[horn blowing]

19:48.291 --> 19:51.625
[Dwarves chanting] Durin! Durin! Durin!

19:51.708 --> 19:55.250
Durin! Durin! Durin!

19:55.333 --> 20:00.041
-Durin! Durin! Durin! Durin!
-[thuds]

20:00.208 --> 20:03.125
-Durin! Durin!
-[chanting stops]

20:05.666 --> 20:06.791
[clanks]

20:08.375 --> 20:10.583
-[Dwarves exclaim]
-[grunts, cheers]

20:10.666 --> 20:15.125
[Dwarves cheering]

20:21.208 --> 20:22.791
Here we go, Elf.

20:23.541 --> 20:24.625
[Dwarves exclaim]

20:37.125 --> 20:38.041
[panting]

20:41.375 --> 20:44.416
-[scraping]
-[gasps]

20:50.958 --> 20:53.500
[breathing heavily]

20:54.750 --> 20:56.875
[grunts] Mm.

20:59.083 --> 21:01.958
[voices whispering]

21:02.833 --> 21:03.833
Hello?

21:04.208 --> 21:06.666
-[shouting echoes]
-[whooshing]

21:06.750 --> 21:09.375
Wait! Wait, it's me!

21:09.833 --> 21:11.208
It's me! Stop!

21:11.375 --> 21:13.375
-[birds screeching]
-[trees creaking]

21:13.458 --> 21:15.250
Wait!

21:15.750 --> 21:18.750
I helped you last night.
You remember me, don't you?

21:18.833 --> 21:20.541
[voices whispering]

21:21.083 --> 21:22.166
Don't you?

21:22.250 --> 21:25.958
[whispering continues]

21:30.708 --> 21:32.208
[wind dwindles]

21:32.291 --> 21:33.416
Okay.

21:33.541 --> 21:36.416
[breathing heavily]

21:36.500 --> 21:37.833
How 'bout this then...

21:38.375 --> 21:39.958
I won't harm you.

21:41.291 --> 21:43.916
You won't harm me. Deal?

21:51.708 --> 21:53.875
Well, that's a start then, isn't it?

21:53.958 --> 21:56.250
Now, proper things first.
Father always says,

21:56.333 --> 22:00.750
"A Harfoot without manners is as like to
get far in life as a square wheel." So...

22:01.833 --> 22:03.250
I'm Nori.

22:08.250 --> 22:09.458
I'm Nori.

22:10.916 --> 22:13.333
[mumbling] I...

22:14.416 --> 22:15.583
No, I'm Nori.

22:15.666 --> 22:17.416
[mumbles] No, I'm Nori.

22:17.500 --> 22:20.041
What about your name? You?

22:23.458 --> 22:25.083
You don't remember, do you?

22:26.875 --> 22:28.666
Suppose you did fall quite a long way.

22:28.750 --> 22:30.958
Anybody's head would be
a bit higgledy-piggledy.

22:31.041 --> 22:32.375
I fell out of a tree once.

22:32.500 --> 22:35.375
For a whole week,
I kept calling strawberries "pigberries."

22:35.458 --> 22:37.541
Can you imagine? A pigberry?

22:40.708 --> 22:41.833
It's food.

22:41.916 --> 22:43.041
[grunts]

22:43.500 --> 22:46.041
They do eat where you're from, don't they?

22:46.125 --> 22:48.625
Of course they do, Nori,
what a silly question.

22:49.666 --> 22:50.666
[grunts]

22:55.208 --> 22:56.291
[grunts]

22:56.375 --> 22:59.916
Mm. [licking]

23:01.291 --> 23:04.541
[licking]

23:18.958 --> 23:19.875
Hmm.

23:21.750 --> 23:23.041
[crunching]

23:23.125 --> 23:25.583
[stammers] No... That's not how you...

23:25.666 --> 23:27.041
[grunting]

23:29.625 --> 23:31.041
[crunching]

23:33.125 --> 23:35.875
-Largo! Largo!
-[lively chatter, laughter]

23:36.666 --> 23:38.666
Leave him, Malva. Why don't you help?

23:38.750 --> 23:41.333
I am helping by asking him to help.

23:42.083 --> 23:44.625
Aw, stop your lounge-a-daising
and lend us a foot.

23:44.708 --> 23:48.166
Well, I think Nori was looking forward
to helping out with that.

23:48.250 --> 23:50.916
Nori? Nori?

23:53.875 --> 23:55.291
[crunching]

23:55.625 --> 23:57.583
Where is it you're from, anyway?

23:57.666 --> 24:00.125
Where do you belong?
Where are all the others?

24:00.208 --> 24:02.041
You know, of your kind? Like you?

24:04.750 --> 24:06.166
Are there any others?

24:22.333 --> 24:25.375
-And up she goes...
-[Harfoots grunting]

24:26.041 --> 24:27.166
Come on, big fella.

24:27.541 --> 24:28.625
[laughing]

24:28.708 --> 24:29.750
[grunts]

24:29.833 --> 24:31.916
-[rope creaking]
-[Malva] Put your back into it, lads!

24:32.000 --> 24:34.500
-[scraping]
-[breathing heavily]

24:39.541 --> 24:40.541
What is it?

24:41.625 --> 24:42.708
[in other language]  Mana...

24:43.500 --> 24:44.916
Is it some sort of map?

24:45.250 --> 24:46.375
[Malva] Come on, lads!

24:46.458 --> 24:48.000
-[Largo grunting]
-[Sadoc laughing]

24:49.000 --> 24:50.500
[Malva] It's got space.

24:50.583 --> 24:52.875
Mana... Mana...

24:52.958 --> 24:54.625
[breathing heavily]

