25:28.125 --> 25:29.541
I'm just a Harfoot!

25:31.333 --> 25:32.416
[panting]

25:32.500 --> 25:33.583
-[Poppy] Nori!
-[gasps]

25:35.708 --> 25:37.791
[shouting]

25:38.041 --> 25:39.666
[Nori] Friend!

25:40.666 --> 25:43.333
Friend. Just a friend.

25:43.916 --> 25:45.000
Nori.

25:46.291 --> 25:47.708
It's your father.

25:49.250 --> 25:51.125
[Largo groans]

25:51.208 --> 25:54.708
Wow! Blueberry indeed. [laughs]

25:55.625 --> 25:56.625
[sighs]

25:57.416 --> 25:59.291
Nori, I'm fine.

25:59.375 --> 26:01.958
I... I slipped on wet grass is all.
It's just a twist.

26:02.041 --> 26:04.333
There's nothing to worry... [groans]

26:04.416 --> 26:05.958
-[Nori] Mam...
-Never you mind.

26:06.041 --> 26:07.208
I should've been here.

26:07.291 --> 26:08.750
[Marigold] You're here now, all right?

26:08.833 --> 26:10.958
Now, go on, fetch me
some cold water and some salt.

26:12.208 --> 26:15.750
[indistinct chatter]

26:24.250 --> 26:27.250
How bad is it? Can he migrate?

26:27.333 --> 26:29.291
[sniffling]

26:29.375 --> 26:31.083
[indistinct chatter]

26:32.666 --> 26:33.708
You saw him.

26:33.791 --> 26:36.166
Couldn't put the weight of a leaf
on that leg.

26:36.250 --> 26:39.250
-Much less pull a cart.
-Mind your own fire, Malva.

26:40.541 --> 26:42.458
[exclaiming sarcastically]

27:06.166 --> 27:07.625
[bellowing echoes]

27:07.708 --> 27:09.416
[gasping]

27:39.250 --> 27:40.291
[Galadriel] Over here!

27:43.083 --> 27:44.208
[panting]

27:46.125 --> 27:48.250
Come. Come closer.

27:48.333 --> 27:51.625
-What do you think you're doing?
-I'm not leaving her adrift.

27:51.708 --> 27:53.958
[man] Suppose you'll be sharing
your rations?

27:54.041 --> 27:55.958
The tides of fate are flowing.

27:56.041 --> 27:57.041
[woman] If no one else will.

27:57.125 --> 27:59.375
Yours may be heading in, or out.

27:59.458 --> 28:02.666
[woman] Refuse to bring her aboard,
and her death will be on our hands.

28:02.750 --> 28:05.791
[man] Didn't seem bothered
when we was debating Doble's death.

28:05.875 --> 28:08.291
Cruelty will not be our deliverance.

28:09.000 --> 28:10.083
[man] Don't let her on.

28:10.791 --> 28:11.625
[woman] Pull her up.

28:13.083 --> 28:14.083
[grunts]

28:14.750 --> 28:16.500
[panting]

28:21.416 --> 28:22.250
[man] No.

28:23.708 --> 28:25.000
Answers first.

28:29.791 --> 28:31.041
Why are you out here?

28:33.041 --> 28:34.875
I was separated from my ship.

28:34.958 --> 28:36.166
Attacked?

28:36.250 --> 28:38.250
[woman 2 whimpering hysterically]

28:38.833 --> 28:40.250
Then you've not seen it?

28:40.666 --> 28:41.916
Seen what?

28:44.916 --> 28:46.208
[whimpering hysterically]

28:46.916 --> 28:48.083
The worm.

28:51.166 --> 28:53.166
We set out two weeks ago, sailing...

28:53.250 --> 28:55.708
-Need we tell her all our affairs?
-[woman] Why not?

28:55.875 --> 28:57.500
Does she look dangerous to you?

28:57.583 --> 28:59.000
Looks can be deceiving.

29:03.708 --> 29:04.875
An Elf.

29:04.958 --> 29:06.791
Remove your hand from me, sir.

29:07.583 --> 29:08.958
You liar.

29:09.041 --> 29:11.458
-We're saved. We're saved. Look!
-[woman] Hurry!

29:11.541 --> 29:13.250
[screaming] Look! Over here!

29:13.333 --> 29:14.500
Help us!

29:14.583 --> 29:17.208
Hurry, help me build a torch. Hurry!

29:17.291 --> 29:19.500
Wait! Until we can see the sails.

29:19.583 --> 29:22.458
Corsairs prowl these waters.
Do you want to be skinned alive?

29:22.541 --> 29:23.375
[gasps]

29:27.833 --> 29:29.666
That's no corsair ship.

29:29.750 --> 29:32.041
That's our ship.

29:38.208 --> 29:39.208
The worm!

29:43.458 --> 29:44.583
Be still.

29:46.125 --> 29:48.208
[bellowing]

30:00.500 --> 30:02.250
-[water gushing]
-[all screaming]

30:04.916 --> 30:07.083
-The Elf led it right to us.
-[Galadriel shouts]

30:20.875 --> 30:22.666
[people shouting]

30:26.750 --> 30:27.583
[man] It's coming!

30:27.666 --> 30:30.458
[people shouting]

30:34.083 --> 30:35.083
[woman screaming] Help!

30:36.541 --> 30:38.041
-[crashes]
-[people scream]

30:48.166 --> 30:49.333
[splashing]

31:02.875 --> 31:05.125
[breathing heavily]

31:28.791 --> 31:29.833
[gasps]

31:39.958 --> 31:41.791
[panting]

31:45.833 --> 31:46.666
[grunts]

31:52.000 --> 31:53.666
[both grunting]

32:01.125 --> 32:02.125
What are you called?

32:02.208 --> 32:05.250
[panting]

32:10.166 --> 32:11.250
Galadriel.

32:13.166 --> 32:14.333
I'm Halbrand.

32:15.250 --> 32:16.458
What's our heading?

32:20.750 --> 32:21.875
[Dwarves cheer]

32:22.083 --> 32:23.083
[Dwarves cheer]

32:24.625 --> 32:25.666
[grunts]

32:26.083 --> 32:26.958
[grunts]

32:27.041 --> 32:28.291
[Dwarves cheer]

32:28.375 --> 32:30.916
[both grunting]

32:31.000 --> 32:32.000
[laughing]

32:32.083 --> 32:33.000
[grunts]

32:33.083 --> 32:34.541
[Dwarves cheer]

32:36.708 --> 32:41.041
[Dwarves cheering and laughing]

32:41.458 --> 32:42.375
[laughs]

32:50.208 --> 32:52.083
-[grunts]
-[Dwarves cheering]

32:52.208 --> 32:55.166
[laughing]

32:55.875 --> 32:57.416
[chuckles]

33:25.375 --> 33:27.916
[Dwarves cheering]

33:28.500 --> 33:30.250
[shouts]

33:31.375 --> 33:32.583
Yes!

33:32.666 --> 33:35.958
[Dwarves chanting] Durin! Durin! Durin!

33:36.041 --> 33:39.291
Durin! Durin! Durin!

33:39.375 --> 33:45.000
Durin! Durin! Durin! Durin! Durin!

33:45.416 --> 33:47.208
A dog may bark at the moon.

33:49.083 --> 33:50.875
But he cannot bring it down.

33:52.416 --> 33:53.750
Take your leave.

33:55.875 --> 33:58.708
Perhaps His Lordship would be willing
to escort me to the exit?

34:01.958 --> 34:03.125
Gladly.

34:03.375 --> 34:05.916
[lift clicking, creaking]

34:15.083 --> 34:18.958
Remarkable. I never dreamed
to find your city so changed.

34:20.250 --> 34:22.041
Now, 20 years will do that.

34:22.125 --> 34:23.625
Has it been only 20?

34:26.208 --> 34:28.458
You must tell me your secret.

34:30.791 --> 34:32.375
Our secrets are our own.

34:33.041 --> 34:34.125
Durin, have I offended you?

34:34.208 --> 34:36.250
To answer that, we'd need a longer lift.

34:36.333 --> 34:38.541
If you wish to discharge me
without explanation,

34:38.625 --> 34:41.041
-that is your choice.
-You bet your feathery shirts it is.

34:41.125 --> 34:43.333
But before squandering
the best opportunity

34:43.416 --> 34:45.500
any Dwarf-prince has had in a generation,

34:45.583 --> 34:47.833
you might at least listen
to the proposal I bring.

34:47.916 --> 34:49.000
Ah, there it is.

34:49.083 --> 34:51.250
The true purpose of your visit.
You want something.

34:51.333 --> 34:53.750
I journeyed here to see my friend,
whom I've greatly missed.

34:53.833 --> 34:56.291
Missed? You missed my wedding.

34:56.375 --> 34:59.375
The birth of my children, two of them!

35:01.250 --> 35:05.583
You cannot barge into my mountain
and demand I welcome you with open arms.

35:06.083 --> 35:08.916
You cannot claim that which you discarded.

35:09.000 --> 35:10.291
Discarded? Durin, I...

35:10.375 --> 35:13.458
Twenty years might be
the blink of an eye to an Elf.

35:14.333 --> 35:16.833
But I've lived an entire life
in that time.

35:18.875 --> 35:20.375
A life you missed.

35:24.916 --> 35:25.875
[grumbles]

35:28.458 --> 35:29.708
[thuds]

35:30.458 --> 35:31.708
[Prince Durin scoffs]

35:33.208 --> 35:35.458
So, what do you have to say to that...

35:37.500 --> 35:38.625
"Friend?"

35:44.208 --> 35:45.416
Congratulations.

35:47.541 --> 35:50.333
On your wife, your children.

35:52.666 --> 35:54.666
I hope you can come to forgive me.

35:57.041 --> 36:01.083
And I would like very much
to apologize to your family as well.

36:04.875 --> 36:05.916
Hmm.

36:06.458 --> 36:08.583
One apology to Disa and you're off.

36:08.666 --> 36:10.666
No getting better acquainted.

36:10.750 --> 36:15.458
No reminiscing about the past.
And absolutely no staying for dinner.

36:15.541 --> 36:17.000
Understood.

36:17.083 --> 36:19.500
[Disa] AulÃ«'s beard! No!

36:19.583 --> 36:21.375
This cannot be Elrond, can it?

36:21.458 --> 36:24.708
I fear so, fair lady.

36:26.291 --> 36:28.416
[exclaiming heartily]

36:30.208 --> 36:31.250
[grumbles]

36:31.333 --> 36:33.583
Durin didn't tell me you were coming.

36:33.666 --> 36:34.958
Durin didn't know.

36:35.041 --> 36:38.291
I've been remiss in not visiting sooner.

36:38.375 --> 36:41.666
An oversight, for which I am here
to humbly ask forgiveness.

36:41.750 --> 36:44.041
-You're staying for dinner.
-He's leaving.

36:44.125 --> 36:45.708
-He's staying.
-He's leaving!

36:45.791 --> 36:46.708
[sternly] He's staying.

36:46.833 --> 36:49.166
-[children laughing]
-[Disa laughs]

36:49.333 --> 36:53.500
Hey! I told you two
to stay out of my heads!

36:53.583 --> 36:57.041
[Disa] And I told you wee monsters
to stay in bed.

36:57.125 --> 36:57.958
Oh, come on!

36:58.208 --> 37:01.458
Gerda! Gamli! Come on, hurry along.

37:01.541 --> 37:02.416
[Gerda] Ow!

37:02.500 --> 37:04.791
Make yourself comfortable, please.

37:05.541 --> 37:07.000
But not too comfortable.

37:08.125 --> 37:09.208
[Disa] Gamli, please.

37:09.291 --> 37:12.083
[Prince Durin] It's off to the salt mines
the both of ya!

37:12.166 --> 37:15.166
Cave-trolls and stalagmite spiders galore!

37:15.250 --> 37:16.666
[Disa and Prince Durin laughing]

37:25.333 --> 37:27.666
[Elrond] How did you two
first become acquainted?

37:28.166 --> 37:31.250
I was resonating a freshly-opened chamber,

37:31.333 --> 37:34.625
fairly confident we were
onto a sizable silver deposit...

37:34.708 --> 37:37.208
"Resonating?"
I've not heard of resonating.

37:37.291 --> 37:39.291
It's when we sing to the stone.

37:39.375 --> 37:41.708
You see, a mountain's like a person.

37:41.791 --> 37:46.208
It's a long and ever-changing story
made of countless small parts.

37:46.291 --> 37:48.958
-Earth and ore, air and water.
-[slurping loudly]

37:49.041 --> 37:53.750
Sing to it properly, each of those parts
will reflect your song back to you,

37:53.833 --> 37:57.166
telling you its story,
showing you what might be hidden,

37:57.250 --> 37:59.708
where to mine, where to tunnel, and...

37:59.791 --> 38:02.333
And where to leave the mountain untouched.

38:02.416 --> 38:04.250
It is a beautiful tradition.

38:04.833 --> 38:07.208
[burps and sighs]

38:07.916 --> 38:12.375
Anyway, we're unpacking our tools,
and my team suddenly grows quiet.

38:12.458 --> 38:14.750
Then, I see our prince.

38:14.833 --> 38:16.666
He's come to check on us.

38:16.750 --> 38:18.791
Far below his purview, mind you.

38:19.250 --> 38:21.083
First, I thought it merely curious.

38:21.500 --> 38:24.083
That is, until he showed up
at our next survey.

38:24.166 --> 38:25.291
[chuckles]

38:25.375 --> 38:29.458
And the one after that.
And the one after that.

38:29.541 --> 38:31.416
Always did have a talent for lurking.

38:31.500 --> 38:34.875
[laughs] Took weeks before he worked up
the courage to court me proper.

38:34.958 --> 38:36.833
Two weeks at most.

38:36.916 --> 38:39.041
-It was five.
-[Prince Durin] You're lying.

38:39.125 --> 38:40.333
She's lying.

38:40.416 --> 38:42.625
She may play coy now,

38:42.708 --> 38:46.583
but she was a moon-eyed girl in love
from the moment we met.

38:46.666 --> 38:47.541
Oof!

38:47.708 --> 38:49.500
-Mmm!
-[Elrond laughs]

38:50.500 --> 38:52.583
A very happy match, indeed.

38:52.666 --> 38:54.458
Should've been at the wedding.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.166
Enough.

38:57.625 --> 38:59.791
-Your friend is here now.
-[slurping]

39:00.041 --> 39:02.041
Can we not take joy in that?

39:02.125 --> 39:03.541
He's not here for us.

39:03.625 --> 39:06.125
His king sent him here
to take what's ours.

39:06.208 --> 39:09.041
To the contrary.
Coming to Khazad-dÃ»m was my idea.

39:09.125 --> 39:11.250
And I have asked for nothing but your ear.

39:11.333 --> 39:13.166
Aye, and that's how it starts.

39:13.250 --> 39:16.250
And soon enough,
we're left with our thumbs in our eyes.

39:16.333 --> 39:19.166
-Elves for Elves, no?
-Has it ever been so between us?

39:19.250 --> 39:21.875
-I don't know! Has it?
-AulÃ«'s beard!

39:24.333 --> 39:26.458
Can you not find a way to mend this?

39:26.541 --> 39:28.875
[Prince Durin breathing heavily]

39:33.875 --> 39:35.708
I see you planted the sapling.

39:36.625 --> 39:39.083
Planted it. Raised it up.

39:39.625 --> 39:42.416
Tends it like it's our third child.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.250
What sort of tree is it, exactly?

39:46.041 --> 39:49.500
A seedling of our Great Tree in Lindon.

39:50.000 --> 39:52.875
The very symbol
of our people's strength and vitality.

39:53.208 --> 39:54.916
[Disa] Some called him a fool

39:55.583 --> 39:58.583
for believing it would grow
in such darkness.

39:58.666 --> 40:01.000
Where there is love,
it is never truly dark.

40:02.041 --> 40:05.000
How could it not grow
in a home like yours?

40:14.166 --> 40:15.916
You're not leaving already?

40:16.000 --> 40:18.500
I fear I've overstayed my welcome.

40:18.583 --> 40:21.208
Thank you, Disa, for your hospitality.

40:23.125 --> 40:24.375
Durin.

40:27.791 --> 40:28.750
[grunts]

40:30.041 --> 40:31.083
[sighs]

40:32.000 --> 40:33.458
Sod it, sit down.

40:34.625 --> 40:37.416
-Please. I hardly wish to intrude.
-I said sit.

40:37.500 --> 40:38.583
Are you certain?

40:38.666 --> 40:42.416
No. And I'm still angry.
Tell me about your king's proposal

40:42.500 --> 40:45.291
so I can decide whether
to present it to my father

40:45.375 --> 40:47.708
or toss it in the nearest slag pit.

41:12.625 --> 41:14.250
You needn't keep your distance.

41:17.083 --> 41:20.333
I am simply wondering what manner of man

41:20.416 --> 41:23.458
would so readily abandon
his companions to death.

41:23.791 --> 41:25.875
The sort that knows how to survive.

41:26.625 --> 41:28.583
Why be part of the larger target?

41:28.666 --> 41:30.166
You are a target still.

41:31.500 --> 41:34.500
I doubt we shall find safety
until we make landfall.

41:34.583 --> 41:37.000
I suspect finding safety
won't be that easy.

41:37.500 --> 41:39.125
Leastways not for you.

41:40.458 --> 41:42.375
"Separated" from your ship.

41:43.791 --> 41:44.833
Really?

41:45.958 --> 41:48.708
-You're a deserter, aren't you?
-Do I have the look of a deserter?

41:48.791 --> 41:52.208
You don't have the look of someone
to whom things happen by accident.

41:53.208 --> 41:55.083
Which means you were running.

41:55.166 --> 41:58.458
Whether toward or from something,
I haven't yet decided.

41:58.541 --> 42:00.875
Duty demanded I return to Middle-earth.

42:02.083 --> 42:04.375
And that is all you need to know.

42:04.458 --> 42:08.250
-Important Elf business, no doubt.
-What have Elves ever done to you?

42:08.333 --> 42:10.583
Do you blame us
for your being stranded here?

42:10.666 --> 42:13.875
The way I see it, it wasn't Elves
that chased me from my homeland.

42:15.375 --> 42:16.541
It was Orcs.

42:18.916 --> 42:19.791
[blazing]

42:25.458 --> 42:28.500
Your home. Where was it?

42:30.208 --> 42:31.708
What's it matter?

42:32.791 --> 42:33.833
It's ashes now.

42:37.208 --> 42:39.541
I know something of the pain you carry.

42:41.208 --> 42:42.291
I grieve for you.

42:47.125 --> 42:48.541
For those you lost.

42:55.125 --> 42:56.500
Around your neck.

42:58.250 --> 43:00.250
Was that the mark of your people's king?

43:00.333 --> 43:02.291
-My people have no king.
-But if they did,

43:02.375 --> 43:05.000
-where might that kingdom be found?
-To what end?

43:05.083 --> 43:07.416
What if I told you we might be able
to reclaim it?

43:07.500 --> 43:10.083
-[scoffs] I'm afraid you're short an army.
-Leave the army to me.

43:10.166 --> 43:11.750
Why're you dodging the question?

43:11.833 --> 43:13.208
Why're you stranded at sea?

43:13.291 --> 43:15.666
Because rather than rest in glory,
I chose to seek out

43:15.750 --> 43:18.125
the very enemy responsible
for your suffering.

43:18.208 --> 43:21.583
Look, Elf. You didn't cause my suffering
and you can't fix it.

43:21.666 --> 43:25.083
No matter how strong your will.
Or your pride.

43:26.791 --> 43:28.166
So let it lie.

43:28.625 --> 43:32.833
I have pursued this foe since
before the first sunrise bloodied the sky.

43:33.416 --> 43:36.083
It would take longer than your lifetime

43:36.166 --> 43:39.500
even to speak the names
of those they have taken from me.

43:40.166 --> 43:43.416
So letting it lie is not an option.

43:46.125 --> 43:49.791
At last, a little honesty.

43:49.875 --> 43:53.125
If you want to murder Orcs
and settle a score, that's your affair.

43:53.208 --> 43:54.875
Don't dress it up as heroism.

43:54.958 --> 43:57.291
Are you going to tell me
where the enemy is or not?

43:57.375 --> 43:58.541
The Southlands.

43:59.125 --> 44:00.166
[sighs]

44:02.041 --> 44:04.208
I need to know how many the enemy were,

44:04.291 --> 44:06.000
under whose banner they marched,

44:06.083 --> 44:09.875
and then you are going to take me
to their last-known location.

44:10.916 --> 44:12.541
I've got my own plans, Elf.

44:14.333 --> 44:18.000
[thunder breaking]

44:18.750 --> 44:22.291
[wind whooshing]

44:22.375 --> 44:23.458
Prepare yourself.

44:45.500 --> 44:47.791
-Watch it!
-[man] Easy now, love.

44:51.333 --> 44:53.375
-[chopping]
-What do you mean, "no bodies?"

44:53.458 --> 44:55.375
I mean the entire village was empty.

44:55.458 --> 44:59.000
It was as if the ground has swallowed up
the people of Hordern like flies.

44:59.083 --> 45:01.458
The ground here is tetchy.
Always has been.

45:01.541 --> 45:04.333
And Crookfinger Lake's
always seepin' vapors.

45:04.416 --> 45:06.000
-Mmm.
-[Bronwyn] I saw a tunnel.

45:06.083 --> 45:07.541
Dug deep, and with care.

45:07.625 --> 45:10.791
By what, I cannot say,
but they were digging towards us.

45:10.875 --> 45:13.250
I tell you, we remain here at our peril.

45:13.333 --> 45:14.750
We must spread the word.

45:14.833 --> 45:17.500
-[chops]
-No! I will not have this gossip, Bronwyn.

45:17.583 --> 45:20.958
I've seen landslides less dangerous
than a wayward tongue,

45:21.041 --> 45:24.625
and without proof or puddin',
that's all it'd be.

45:24.708 --> 45:27.125
Waldreg, we're all alone.

45:27.208 --> 45:29.750
Ostirith is empty.
The watchtower abandoned.

45:29.833 --> 45:31.791
Yes, I know,
and I'm not invitin' them Elves

45:31.875 --> 45:33.708
back on account of some sinkhole.

45:33.791 --> 45:37.791
Havin' them gone is a relief.
Well, for most of us, anyhow.

45:56.833 --> 45:58.708
[creaking]

46:00.791 --> 46:02.041
Bloody mice.

46:04.333 --> 46:06.625
[grunting]

46:06.708 --> 46:09.833
-[thudding]
-Stupid, bastard mice!

46:09.916 --> 46:11.166
[grunting]

46:18.708 --> 46:19.583
[screams]

46:22.333 --> 46:26.250
[rustling]

46:44.750 --> 46:47.666
[gasping]

46:53.833 --> 46:54.708
[grunts]

47:02.083 --> 47:03.333
[stones falling in distance]

47:10.833 --> 47:12.250
[voices whispering]

47:19.041 --> 47:20.375
[stones falling]

47:29.000 --> 47:30.375
-[growling echoes]
-[gasps]

47:35.458 --> 47:36.375
[growling]

47:43.750 --> 47:45.583
[rats squeaking]

47:48.500 --> 47:49.875
[grunting frantically]

47:54.458 --> 47:56.125
[rapid rustling]

47:57.833 --> 47:58.875
[exclaims]

48:10.583 --> 48:11.708
[gasping]

48:18.583 --> 48:19.875
[grunting]

48:27.125 --> 48:30.625
[breathing heavily]

48:31.875 --> 48:33.041
[bubbling]

48:42.083 --> 48:43.833
[breathing heavily]

48:43.916 --> 48:45.083
[crumbling]

48:45.958 --> 48:48.375
[panting]

49:16.208 --> 49:17.291
Theo?

49:19.875 --> 49:21.083
Theo?

49:24.166 --> 49:25.000
[door opens]

49:34.375 --> 49:35.458
[shushing]

49:35.541 --> 49:37.541
[whispering] Theo, what's wrong?
What happened?

49:37.625 --> 49:39.250
Get help. Go.

49:41.333 --> 49:43.833
[thudding, scraping]

49:43.916 --> 49:45.041
[creaks]

49:58.791 --> 50:01.541
[stones falling]

50:02.375 --> 50:03.791
[clatter]

50:03.875 --> 50:07.000
[panting]

50:11.291 --> 50:16.458
[raspy breathing]

50:16.541 --> 50:19.416
[panting]

50:21.375 --> 50:23.083
[bones creaking]

50:23.166 --> 50:25.250
[raspy breathing]

50:26.041 --> 50:28.166
[shuddering]

50:28.833 --> 50:32.875
[raspy breathing]

50:36.958 --> 50:40.166
[sniffing rapidly]

50:40.250 --> 50:44.125
-[footsteps approaching]
-[floorboards creaking]

50:45.916 --> 50:49.666
[shuddering]

50:50.500 --> 50:53.541
[floorboard creaking]

51:04.875 --> 51:09.625
[clattering]

51:12.250 --> 51:13.750
[objects shattering]

51:15.875 --> 51:17.791
-[loud thud]
-[clattering]

51:20.791 --> 51:23.041
[screaming]

51:23.125 --> 51:24.666
[groans]

51:24.750 --> 51:26.416
-[slashes]
-[groans]

51:26.500 --> 51:27.791
[growling]

51:27.875 --> 51:29.125
[groaning]

51:29.541 --> 51:31.666
-Theo, run!
-[grunting]

51:31.750 --> 51:33.083
[grunting]

51:33.166 --> 51:35.208
-[thudding]
-[groaning]

51:35.583 --> 51:37.291
Hey! [grunts]

51:37.375 --> 51:39.625
-[gas hisses]
-[groaning]

51:41.541 --> 51:42.416
[growling]

51:44.416 --> 51:45.333
[Theo] Stop!

51:47.250 --> 51:48.958
-[screaming]
-[crashing]

51:49.041 --> 51:50.125
[snarling]

51:51.375 --> 51:53.916
-[shouting]
-[groans]

51:54.000 --> 51:55.458
-[groans]
-[thuds]

51:55.541 --> 51:57.208
[metal clinking]

51:57.291 --> 52:00.833
-[growling]
-[grunting]

52:03.541 --> 52:05.041
[Theo shouting]

52:05.125 --> 52:08.083
[choking]

52:10.958 --> 52:12.291
[groaning loudly]

52:12.375 --> 52:14.375
-[coughing]
-[growling]

52:20.958 --> 52:23.416
[shouting]

52:24.083 --> 52:25.916
-[all exclaim]
-[panting]

52:26.958 --> 52:29.625
If there are any of you here
who want to live,

52:29.708 --> 52:32.208
we make for the Elven tower
at first light.

52:41.083 --> 52:45.083
-[thunder breaking]
-[waves crashing]

52:50.166 --> 52:53.375
We need to tie the boat!
It's coming apart!

52:53.458 --> 52:54.708
The wind is too strong.

52:54.791 --> 52:56.125
[Halbrand] Grab the ropes!

53:02.125 --> 53:04.958
[grunting]

53:16.333 --> 53:18.583
[grunting]

53:19.708 --> 53:22.416
Come on! Give me your hand!

53:22.500 --> 53:23.458
[grunts]

53:24.958 --> 53:26.625
Bind yourself to me!

53:26.708 --> 53:28.750
Come on! Give me your hand!

53:28.875 --> 53:30.541
[thunder breaks]

53:30.625 --> 53:31.666
[groans]

54:34.541 --> 54:35.875
[gasping]

54:43.500 --> 54:45.541
[both grunting]

54:49.083 --> 54:50.333
[breathing heavily]

54:53.875 --> 54:54.750
[both grunting]

55:09.250 --> 55:13.166
[The Stranger breathing deeply]

55:27.041 --> 55:29.958
Hello? It's me. It's me, Nori.

55:30.041 --> 55:34.000
[breathing deeply]

55:40.500 --> 55:45.041
You see, the next migration is in just
a few days now, and everything's gone...

55:45.833 --> 55:47.500
Three rabbits to the moon.

55:50.541 --> 55:52.125
I wanted to help you.

55:53.875 --> 55:55.875
I thought I could, but I'm sorry.

55:55.958 --> 56:00.500
[breathing heavily]

56:02.500 --> 56:04.083
[gasps]

56:08.958 --> 56:11.958
It's a lantern. We use fireflies.

56:12.041 --> 56:15.041
[breathing heavily]

56:15.125 --> 56:17.458
[fireflies trilling]

56:18.291 --> 56:19.250
[exclaiming]

56:38.541 --> 56:39.958
[whispering in other language]

56:40.750 --> 56:42.708
[gasping]

56:47.208 --> 56:49.666
[whispering in other language]

56:59.666 --> 57:01.333
What's he saying to them?

57:03.625 --> 57:05.333
I don't speak firefly.

57:11.833 --> 57:14.333
[whispering continues]

57:35.458 --> 57:37.125
They're stars.

57:38.166 --> 57:41.125
A kind of constellation.

57:42.041 --> 57:45.583
Okay? They're stars? What does that mean?

57:45.666 --> 57:47.083
[Nori] This is how we help him.

57:47.166 --> 57:50.041
He wants us to help him find those stars.

57:51.875 --> 57:53.291
[whispers] That's it, isn't it?

57:54.208 --> 57:55.416
Isn't it?

57:57.916 --> 58:00.458
[panting]

58:05.791 --> 58:07.583
I've never seen those stars before.

58:09.333 --> 58:12.333
But I have a pretty good idea
where I can find them.

58:24.333 --> 58:25.375
[shuddering]

58:25.458 --> 58:26.625
Nori?

58:26.708 --> 58:28.125
[shudders]

58:28.916 --> 58:30.208
[gasps]

58:41.958 --> 58:44.875
I'm certain of it. He doesn't know.

58:49.666 --> 58:50.833
Perhaps.

58:52.666 --> 58:53.833
Perhaps not.

58:57.416 --> 58:59.625
You've always had sandstone
in your granite

58:59.708 --> 59:01.708
as far as the Elves were concerned.

59:01.791 --> 59:04.125
Tell me, do you not think
it's a coincidence

59:04.208 --> 59:07.375
that an Elf should just land
on our doorstep? Now?

59:07.458 --> 59:10.375
I've known Elrond
for half a century, Father.

59:10.458 --> 59:12.750
I'd sense it if he were hiding something.

59:12.875 --> 59:16.500
Perhaps he sensed that it was you
who was hiding something.

59:16.583 --> 59:18.375
You think too much of their kind.

59:18.833 --> 59:21.416
We're the ones holding
the long end of the hammer here.

59:22.250 --> 59:24.541
Aye. For now.

59:28.791 --> 59:30.750
[Prince Durin]
Elrond is a friend. I trust him.

59:30.833 --> 59:33.500
[King Durin] There can be no trust
between hammer and rock.

59:34.166 --> 59:38.041
Eventually one or the other
must surely break.

59:43.166 --> 59:44.750
[creaking]

59:59.208 --> 1:00:02.208
[crickets chirping]

1:00:32.208 --> 1:00:36.208
[oozing]

1:00:38.625 --> 1:00:44.625
[hissing, sizzling]

1:00:54.125 --> 1:00:55.083
[Bronwyn] Theo!

1:00:59.500 --> 1:01:00.500
You ready?

1:01:00.916 --> 1:01:03.250
Yes, Mother. I'm ready.

1:01:03.666 --> 1:01:05.250
[blowing]

1:01:34.750 --> 1:01:39.541
[footsteps]

1:01:41.250 --> 1:01:44.791
[shuddering]

1:01:55.583 --> 1:01:58.375
[panting]
